								<p class="newsHead">Partnership model could be unsustainable in property market says Optima Legal</p>
								<p class="newsDate">Jan&nbsp;2009</p>
								<p><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Property, legal recoveries and dispute resolution specialist Optima Legal, previously a division of </span><stockticker /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">DLA</span></stockticker /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"> Piper, claims the legal landscape for lender services could be changed forever.</span></strong></p><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal">Announcing £6 million investment programme for 2009 and the recruitment of solicitors and paralegals for its repossession, debt recovery and professional negligence teams Optima Legal has also recently been appointed to deliver a range of legal services for:</p><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><span style="mso-list: Ignore">·<span style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; FONT-VARIANT: normal; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-SIZE: 7pt; FONT-WEIGHT: normal">          </span></span></span><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">National Australia Bank</span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><span style="mso-list: Ignore">·<span style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; FONT-VARIANT: normal; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-SIZE: 7pt; FONT-WEIGHT: normal">          </span></span></span><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Lloyds TSB and C&amp;G</span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><span style="mso-list: Ignore">·<span style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; FONT-VARIANT: normal; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-SIZE: 7pt; FONT-WEIGHT: normal">          </span></span></span><place /><placename /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Leeds</span></placename /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"> </span><placetype /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Building</span></placetype /></place /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"> Society</span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; TEXT-INDENT: -18pt; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt 36pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Symbol; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol"><span style="mso-list: Ignore">·<span style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; FONT-VARIANT: normal; FONT-STYLE: normal; FONT-SIZE: 7pt; FONT-WEIGHT: normal">          </span></span></span><place /><placename /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Britannia</span></placename /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"> </span><placetype /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Building</span></placetype /></place /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"> Society</span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">The firm, which now has over 800 staff across four </span><country-region /><place /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">UK</span></place /></country-region /><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"> offices, has pointed to its unique business model – a completely flexible mix of services, which optimises the use of specialist solicitor advice within a cost-effective and capacity-driven process – as the reason why it is continuing to grow in a tough commercial climate.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Optima Legal Partner Anthony Ruane comments: “The legal landscape is changing fast, particularly in the financial services and property sector. Law firms which adhere to the traditional partnership model, seeking short term gain and unacceptable profit margins, are finding that this approach cannot be sustained in the current market. As a commercial business focused on investing for the long term with no bank debt, we are committed towards cost and risk reduction for clients and the flexibility of our structure means we can deliver counter-cyclical work and adapt quickly as the market dictates. </span></p><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">“We are clearly not immune to fluctuations in property instructions, but because of the nature of our business we are able to change emphasis and redeploy staff as the market dictates. Currently that means a shift to legal recoveries areas in line with market demand. Come the upturn, the balance will return to conveyancing and remortgage.”</span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">The firm’s current growth spate comes on the back of a £30 million investment programme over the past 18 months, acquiring Dickinson Dees’ volume business d3 Legal at the end of last year and previously taking on McKeags in Newcastle, Turner MacFarlane Green in Glasgow and Pathway, the volume legal property services division of Walker Morris.</span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB"></span></p><p /><p style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="LINE-HEIGHT: 150%; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB">Optima Legal will continue to seek acquisition opportunities through 2009, said Anthony, if they added value to the firm’s client base and expanded its multi-jurisdictional offer. The business will also continue to invest heavily in developing its e-conveyancing service to serve an increasingly automated Land Registry process and cater for the next generation of property owners, for whom online transactions will be increasingly the norm.</span></p><p /><p /><p> </p><p /><p> </p><p /><p> </p><p /><p> </p></span></p>
								
								
